The main topics addressed in the 2025 budget include: 
1. the state of the Ghanaian economy in 2024; 
2. macroeconomic policies, targets, and measures for 2025 and the medium-term; 
3. policy initiatives and budget allocations; and 
4. sectoral performance and outlook. 

[Source: budget.pdf | Score: 0.7366]

The state of the Ghanaian economy in 2024 included: 
- Overall real GDP growth rate of 3.1 percent; 
- Overall Non-Oil real GDP growth rate of 2.8 percent; 
- End-period December year-on-year inflation of 15.0 percent; 
- Overall budget deficit (Commitment basis) of 4.2 percent of GDP; 
- Primary balance surplus (Commitment basis) of 0.5 percent of GDP. 
(Budget Document, Page 22)
